fire swept through the lobby of a two-story college dormitory today, forcing many students to jump 20 feet to safety and injuring at least eight students, authorities said
most had just come from a party, so they were awake,'' when the fire broke after midnight in mixon hall, a men's dormitory at chowan college, said police officer bryant cooke
one student was listed in critical condition and another in serious condition at duke university medical center, said trish womble, director of nursing at roanoke-chowan hospital, where six students were treated for minor burns
many students jumped from second-story fire escapes and windows, cooke said. cooke said one student was found unconscious, overcome by smoke, on the second floor. most students had evacuated on their own by the time firefighters arrived
the cause of the fire was still under investigation, but cooke said, ``we're thinking arson.''
