hundreds of campers were evacuated from yosemite national park late thursday and early today when wind topping 60 mph knocked down trees up to 100 feet tall, park spokeswoman mallory smith said
one tree crashed through a cabin and crushed 9-year-old jasmine bitts of garden grove, who was staying with her mother and a companion, who suffered minor injuries
