six people, including a firefighter, were injured when an unfinished apartment building caught fire shortly after midnight, and wind-swept embers spread the blaze to a 10-unit apartment complex and four other buildings
twenty-five to 30 people were left homeless and damage was estimated at $345,000, fire spokesman jim williamson said
in east los angeles, a fire in a commercial building spread to three houses early today, said los angeles county fire spokesman bob haskell. more than 20 people were left homeless
that fire was blamed on electrical wires that were blown into contact over a roofing company, sending sparks into two propane tanks. damage was estimated at $500,000
