police said the bottle exploded in a first-floor bathroom of the university's chemistry department during non-class hours at midday, apparently while the group took part in a prank
joaquin francisco pereda gomez, 22, underwent surgery for serious injuries to his hand at clinico hospital in madrid. a hospital spokeswoman quoted doctors as saying he later may have to have his hand amputated
the others were treated for minor eye and ear injuries and released, the spokeswoman said
a soviet news commentator on friday accused u.s. arms negotiators in geneva of trying to make a ``massive departure'' from an understanding on space defenses reached during the superpower summit
vladimir bogachev blamed the united states for what he called a worsening atmosphere at the geneva talks. the commentary was distributed by the official tass news agency two days before the arrival of secretary of state george p. shultz
among other issues, shultz is to discuss with soviet leader mikhail s. gorbachev and other top officials efforts to cut the superpowers' long-range missiles by 50 percent
the soviet union argues that an understanding on president reagan's ``star wars'' program for a space-based missile defense must be a part of the agreement
they say reagan and gorbachev reached a basis for agreement on strategic weapons and space defenses during their december summit meeting in washington
in recent weeks the situation at the talks has noticeably worsened,'' bogachev said. ``the u.s. side is trying to effect a massive departure from the accords which are explicitly spelled out in the joint statement at the summit level.''
the soviet union claims the ``star wars'' program is a violation of the 1972 anti-ballistic missile treaty
the u.s. delegation in geneva is acting as though reagan and gorbachev did not make any connection between strategic weapons and space defenses in their talks in december, bogachev said
the militarization of outer space according to the `star wars' plans will lead to a sharp destabilization of the military-political situation in the world,'' he said. ``militarization of outer space and a cut in strategic offensive weapons on earth are incompatible.''
he said the united states also was seeking to arm long-range sea-based missiles with conventional warheads, even though the non-nuclear warheads can be replaced quickly with nuclear charges. dollars</head>
