their alleged captors have released two statements in which they accused the two scandinavians of espionage activities. unrwa has blamed their abduction on palestinians acting without political motivation or links to any organization
the afl-cio called friday on honduras to deny use of its territory to nicaraguan contra rebels and said it wants an investigation of allegations that high-ranking honduran military officers are involved in drug trafficking
in an intensely negotiated statement on central america, the u.s. labor federation also condemned what it called the nicaraguan government's continued political imprisonment of 16 trade union leaders
