the nasdaq composite index for the over-the-counter market gained 1.49 to 357.12. at the american stock exchange, the market value index closed at 280.16, up 2.24
the dollar turned in a mixed performance against major foreign currencies friday, failing to hold gains made late in the previous trading session
gold prices rose. republic national bank of new york reported a late bid of $445 for a troy ounce of gold, up from $442.80 late thursday
in the absence of significant news, the dollar finished the day higher than it had been thursday in europe, but lower than the levels attained in thursday's late rally in new york
thursday's rally was attributed to technical factors and president reagan's statement that he wanted to rescue a kidnap victim in lebanon. international tension tends to increase interest in dollars as a safe haven
the dollar dropped friday in europe against the swiss franc after swiss national bank president pierre languetin said he hoped central banks would sell dollars if the american currency rose too sharply, dealers said
otherwise, ``u.s. dollar trading was actually non-existent today,'' said rod fowler, foreign-exchange manager for wood gundy inc. in toronto
at the moment we're in a stalemate situation'' between bulls and bears on the dollar, said david godwin, chief currency dealer for union bank of switzerland in new york
the british pound fell to $1.7505 from $1.7508 in london. later in new york the pound finished at $1.7495, down from earlier in the day but up from its price of $1.7418 late thursday
in tokyo, the dollar rose to a closing 130.53 japanese yen from 130.00 yen on thursday. in later london trading, the dollar slipped to 130.02 yen. by the end of the trading day in new york, the dollar stood at 130.05 yen, down from 130.38 yen late thursday
other late dollar rates in new york, compared with rates late thursday, included: 1.7080 west german marks, down from 1.7123; 1.3980 swiss francs, down from 1.4098; 5.7755 french francs, down from 5.7870; 1,256.75 italian lire, down from 1,261.00; and 1.2737 canadian dollars, up from 1.2706
other late dollar rates in europe, compared with late thursday's prices, included: 1.7075 west german marks, up from 1.7040; 1.3985 swiss francs, down from 1.4010; 5.7675 french francs, up from 5.7555; 1.9150 dutch guilders, up from 1.9130; 1,257.75 italian lire, up from 1,254.63; and 1.2702 canadian dollars, up from 1.2690
gold bullion dropped to $441 in early trading in europe, then rallied somewhat when traders bought dollars either to limit losses or trade in on the metal's earlier decline
